		<td><b>Flash Card to NES Cartridge Adapter</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Apologies if this has been suggested before, but I just thought of something.  Would it be possible to make a NES cartridge that has, say, a secure digital flash memory slot in it, that lets you put ROM files on the flash card, put the flash card into the cartridge, put the cartridge/adapter into a regular NES and play the games as if it were a regular cartridge?  Maybe it would include a custom multi-game menu on a rom that automatically starts up and lets you select the game you want to play.  Also, it could save SRAM data to the flash card.
<br />
<br />I'd pay some real money for that.  I guess the trick would be containing the whole design in a package the size of a NES cartridge.  Maybe Kevtris could tackle it? <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" />
<br />
<br />RedWolf
<br />
<br />---
<br /><a href="http://www.vintagecomputing.com" class="postlink">Vintage Computing and Gaming</a>

		

